<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,618,785]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boggemann" authorityYear="2009" box="[189,451,618,644]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Dysponetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="profundus">
<emphasis box="[189,451,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Dysponetus profundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the 
<collectingCountry box="[855,941,618,644]" name="Angola" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Angola</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1083,618,644]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Guinea</collectingCountry>
Basins, at depths of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.823" metricValueMax="5.654999999999999" metricValueMin="3.991" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="m" value="4823.0" valueMax="5655.0" valueMin="3991.0">3991– 5655 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boggemann M." box="[301,520,653,679]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="252 - 428" refId="ref10033" refString="Boggemann M. 2009. Polychaetes (Annelida) of the abyssal SE Atlantic. Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution 9 (4 - 5): 252 - 428. Available from http: // www. sciencedirect. com / science / journal / 14396092 [accessed 5 Jul. 2019]." type="journal article" year="2009">Böggemann 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens reported here were recovered in hemipelagic silty clay with foraminiferans collected from a topographic high in the vicinity of the SW Iberian margin fault lineaments (
<bibRefCitation author="Hensen C. &amp; Scholz F. &amp; Nuzzo M. &amp; Valadares V. &amp; Gracia E. &amp; Terrinha P. &amp; Liebetrau V. &amp; Kaul N. &amp; Silva S. &amp; Martinez-Loriente S. &amp; Bartolome R. &amp; Pinero E. &amp; Magalhaes V. H. &amp; Schmidt M. &amp; Weise S. M. &amp; Cunha M. &amp; Hilario A. &amp; Perea H. &amp; Rovelli L. &amp; Lackschewitz K." box="[331,558,724,751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="339 - 342" refId="ref10591" refString="Hensen C., Scholz F., Nuzzo M., Valadares V., Gracia E., Terrinha P., Liebetrau V., Kaul N., Silva S., Martinez-Loriente S., Bartolome R., Pinero E., Magalhaes V. H., Schmidt M., Weise S. M., Cunha M., Hilario A., Perea H., Rovelli L. &amp; Lackschewitz K. 2015. Strike-slip faults mediate the rise of crustalderived fluids and mud volcanism in the deep sea. Geology 43 (4): 339 - 342. https: // doi. org / 10.1130 / G 36359.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Hensen 
<emphasis box="[428,487,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). The present study extends the geographical distribution of this species to the Horseshoe Abyssal Plain (SW Iberian margin; 
<figureCitation box="[810,877,759,785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,656,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[189,1398,656,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Map with the locations of the sampling sites. CR = Carlos Ribeiro; HAP = Horseshoe Abyssal Plain; JB = Jezus Baraza; MV = mud volcano." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3353544/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), at a depth of 
<quantity box="[1056,1148,759,785]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.864" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="m" value="4864.0">4864 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
